src.assignment1.addressbook

Class Contact

  • java.lang.Object
    • src.assignment1.addressbook.Contact

  • public class Contact
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is meant to store contact information of a user. The contact information is in the form of name, e-mail address, phone number and notes. The class makes use of builder patter and objects are instantiated using the build function of static class named Builder. The Builder class is also provided by different API with which different fields of a contact can be set. None of the fields in Contact are mandatory. A typical instantiation of Contact would look like: new Contact.Builder().setName("Anurag").setEmailAddress("anurag@gmail.com").setPhoneNumber("987").build();
    Author:
    Anurag
